substep.action:
Open {{session.research_path}} and append a new dated section to its body with {{session.turn_synthesis}}. Format:
## Turn {{turn_number}}: {{session.turn_focus}} ({{ISO 8601 datetime}})
{{session.turn_synthesis}}
### Sources
{{citations}}
Use the Edit tool — do not overwrite the file's frontmatter or prior turn entries.

check.action:
Open {{session.questions_path}} and append a Q&A entry. Format:

## Q{{turn_number}}: {{session.user_question.statement}}

**Asked**: {{ISO 8601 datetime}}
**Mode**: {{session.turn_mode}}

**Answer**: {{session.turn_user_answer.answer}}

**Rejected alternatives**:
- **{{alt_1.label}}**: {{alt_1.why_not}}
- **{{alt_2.label}}**: {{alt_2.why_not}}
...

{{optional: brief note linking to research findings or DRs spawned this turn}}

Use the Edit tool to append. Preserve all prior content.

Append a research-only note to the questions file. Format:

## R{{turn_number}}: {{session.turn_focus}} (research-only)

**Performed**: {{ISO 8601 datetime}}
**Mode**: {{session.turn_mode}}
**Findings recorded**: see research file Turn {{turn_number}}
{{optional: deferred items, e.g., "web research declined"}}

Invoke the ticket-prototype skill via the skill system. Pass context:
- caller_question: {{session.turn_focus}}
- bundle_dir: {{session.bundle_dir}}
- slug: {{session.slug}}
- prior_research: a brief summary of relevant findings already in the research file

Wait for ticket-prototype to return its payload (findings_block,
prototype_path, status, etc.).

substep.output:
Turn {{turn_number}} bundle updates:

- Research file: synthesis appended {{+ prototype findings if turn_prototype_record.status == "answered" or "partially_answered"}}
- Questions file: {{Q-entry or R-entry}} added
- Prototype: {{session.turn_prototype_record.name + status or "(not invoked this turn)"}}
- CONTEXT.md: {{updated with N terms / not touched}}
- Decision Record: {{DR-NNN scaffolded / declined / none surfaced}}
- last_updated stamps: applied to {{count}} files
- Validation: PASS

Proceeding to readiness gate.
